<subSubSection id="88E46522FFB8C324FF0BFA02FBFAFE5D" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="C04136A9FFB8C324FF0BFA02FB7EFECD" blockId="5.[151,1437,1481,2010]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,501]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName id="07FE4D2AFFB8C327FF0BFA02FE18FA48" box="[151,415,1481,1505]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Hemidactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gleadowi">
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFB8C327FF0BFA02FE18FA48" box="[151,415,1481,1505]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Hemidactylus gleadowi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on an undisclosed number of specimens deposited in the collection of the Kurrachee Museum (Karachi, 
<collectingCountry id="B8E97639FFB8C327FD86FA26FDFCF9AC" box="[538,635,1517,1541]" name="Pakistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="A46F4B58FFB8C327FD0DFA26FCBEF9AC" author="Murray" box="[657,825,1517,1541]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" refString="Murray, J. A. (1884 a) The Vertebrate Zoology of Sind. A Systematic Account with Descriptions of all the Known Species of Mammals, Birds, and Reptiles Inhabiting the Province; Observations on Their Habits, &amp; c; Tables of Their Geographic Distribution in Persia, Beloochistan, and Afghanistan; Punjab, North-West Provinces, and the Peninsula of India Generally, with Woodcuts, Lithographs, and Coloured Illustrations. Richardson &amp; Co., London. xvi + 424 pp. + Pl. I - XIII." type="book" year="1884" yearSuffix="a">
Murray 
<number id="7636248EFFB8C327FD6CFA26FCABF9AC" box="[752,812,1517,1541]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="1884.0">1884</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
). No comparison with congeners was provided in this description, however a figure was given (
<figureCitation id="58C52A2CFFB8C327FDEBF9DAFD3EF980" box="[631,697,1553,1577]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1169,1192]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,447,1147]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,447,1147]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 1. Historical figures of the Hemidactylus brookii group taxa: A. H. brookii adult male lectotype (BMNH 1947.3.6.47) by present designation, from Gray (1867: Pl. 15, Fig. 2), later reprinted in Gray (1875: Pl. 15, Fig. 2); B. H. subtriedroides adult male paralectotype (ZSI 4135) by present designation, from Annandale (1905 b: Pl. II, Fig. 1); C. H. gleadowi not based on the original type series, from Boulenger (1890: 86, Fig. 27), later reprinted as H. brookii (Boulenger 1912: 42, Fig. 14; Smith 1935: 90, Fig. 28); D. H. gleadowi a syntype from Murray (1884 a: Fig. 3)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/278833/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">
Fig. 
<number id="7636248EFFB8C327FD32F9DAFD3EF980" box="[686,697,1553,1577]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
D). There appears to be no subsequent literature in which these specimens were examined. Murray did, however, provide a relatively precise 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFB8C327FBBBF9FDFBD0F9E7" box="[1063,1111,1590,1614]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
locality, and for its time, a detailed description of his new species. Furthermore, in 
<number id="7636248EFFB8C327FC90F992FCC3F9D8" box="[780,836,1625,1649]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="1884.0">1884</number>
he provided the British Museum with two specimens which he considered representative of the species, but he did not refer to these specimens specifically as part of the 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFB8C327FF0BF969FF40F913" box="[151,199,1698,1722]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
series (
<bibRefCitation id="A46F4B58FFB8C327FE82F96AFE5EF910" author="Boulenger" box="[286,473,1697,1721]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" refString="Boulenger, G. A. (1885) Catalogue of the Lizards in the British Museum (Natural History). Second Ed.; Volume 1: Gekkonidae, Eublepharidae, Uroplatidae, Pygopodidae, Agamidae. Taylor &amp; Francis, London. xii + 436 pp. + Pl. I - XXXII" type="book" year="1885">
Boulenger 
<number id="7636248EFFB8C327FE01F96AFE5EF910" box="[413,473,1697,1721]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="1885.0">1885</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Murray did not identify 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFB8C327FD63F969FCE6F913" box="[767,865,1698,1722]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">syntypes</typeStatus>
or 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFB8C327FC15F969FC3EF913" box="[905,953,1698,1722]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
series in the original description, thus it is possible that the non-designation of these two specimens as 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFB8C327FCABF90DFCF5F977" box="[823,882,1734,1758]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">types</typeStatus>
may simply have been due to inaccurate communication at the time of their deposition in the British Museum. By examination, these specimens conform to the original description of 
<taxonomicName id="07FE4D2AFFB8C327FE03F8C4FDACF88F" box="[415,555,1806,1830]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Hemidactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gleadowi">
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFB8C327FE03F8C4FDACF88F" box="[415,555,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">H. gleadowi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in all characters. Kurrachee Museum no longer exists, but the 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFB8C327FA9AF8C5FAB1F88F" box="[1286,1334,1806,1830]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
material originally held in that collection were reportedly transferred to the Zoological Survey of 
<collectingCountry id="B8E97639FFB8C327FB19F8FAFB63F8E0" box="[1157,1252,1841,1865]" name="Pakistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(
<collectionCode id="A6EFAE6CFFB8C327FB68F8FAFAA0F8E0" box="[1268,1319,1841,1865]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/wpks-vb9t" name="Zoological Survey of Pakistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">ZSP</collectionCode>
) (R. Masroor 
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFB8C327FF50F89CFE88F8C7" box="[204,271,1878,1902]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">in litt.</emphasis>
<number id="7636248EFFB8C327FE8AF89EFED4F8C4" box="[278,339,1877,1901]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="2009.0">2009</number>
). A recent attempt to locate these specimens by the staff of the 
<collectionCode id="A6EFAE6CFFB8C327FB88F89EFBC3F8C4" box="[1044,1092,1877,1901]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/wpks-vb9t" name="Zoological Survey of Pakistan" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">ZSP</collectionCode>
was unsuccessful (R. Masroor 
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFB8C327FF0BF8B1FF5EF838" box="[151,217,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">in litt.</emphasis>
<number id="7636248EFFB8C327FF7CF8B2FE9BF838" box="[224,284,1913,1937]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="2009.0">2009</number>
), thus I consider the 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFB8C327FD9EF8B1FDB5F83B" box="[514,562,1914,1938]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName id="07FE4D2AFFB8C327FD25F8B1FCC6F838" box="[697,833,1913,1937]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Hemidactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gleadowi">
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFB8C327FD25F8B1FD4AF838" box="[697,717,1914,1937]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFB8C327FD46F8B2FCC6F838" box="[730,833,1913,1937]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">gleadowi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be lost. It is therefore necessary to designate a 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFB8C327FAF6F8B1FF40F81F" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">neotype</typeStatus>
to stabilise the nomenclatural status of the species. The only specimens in existence that can be unambiguously allocated to 
<taxonomicName id="07FE4D2AFFB8C327FEFFF809FE6BF870" box="[355,492,1985,2009]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Hemidactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gleadowi">
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFB8C327FEFFF809FEF0F870" box="[355,375,1986,2009]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFB8C327FE19F80AFE6BF870" box="[389,492,1985,2009]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">gleadowi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are those at 
<collectionCode id="A6EFAE6CFFB8C327FDE5F809FD57F870" box="[633,720,1986,2009]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">BMNH</collectionCode>
, thus I here designate 
<collectionCode id="A6EFAE6CFFB8C327FC55F809FB9AF870" box="[969,1053,1986,2009]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">BMNH</collectionCode>
[
<number id="7636248EFFB8C327FBB7F80AFBC2F870" box="[1067,1093,1985,2009]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42" value="18.0">18</number>
]84.7.25.8 as the 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFB8C327FA96F809FAE1F873" box="[1290,1382,1986,2010]" pageId="5" pageNumber="42">neotype</typeStatus>
. The only issue presented by this action is that the collection locality of the 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFBBC324FC5FFF53FB9BFF19" box="[963,1052,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">neotype</typeStatus>
must be adopted as the new 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFBBC324FAF0FF53FA1BFF19" box="[1388,1436,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
locality in accordance with Article 
<number id="7636248EFFBBC324FD83FF77FDD7FF7D" box="[543,592,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="76.3">76.3</number>
of the I.C.Z.N. (
<number id="7636248EFFBBC324FC95FF77FCC2FF7D" box="[777,837,188,212]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="1999.0">1999</number>
; hereafter referred in text as the “ 
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFBBC324FB25FF77FB73FF7D" box="[1209,1268,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Code</emphasis>
”). In this case, the original 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFBBC324FEBEFF2BFED5FF51" box="[290,338,224,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
locality provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="A46F4B58FFBBC324FDD6FF2BFD79FF5E" author="Murray" box="[586,766,223,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" refString="Murray, J. A. (1884 a) The Vertebrate Zoology of Sind. A Systematic Account with Descriptions of all the Known Species of Mammals, Birds, and Reptiles Inhabiting the Province; Observations on Their Habits, &amp; c; Tables of Their Geographic Distribution in Persia, Beloochistan, and Afghanistan; Punjab, North-West Provinces, and the Peninsula of India Generally, with Woodcuts, Lithographs, and Coloured Illustrations. Richardson &amp; Co., London. xvi + 424 pp. + Pl. I - XIII." type="book" year="1884" yearSuffix="a">
Murray (
<number id="7636248EFFBBC324FD33FF14FD6EFF5E" box="[687,745,223,247]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="1884.0">1884</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
was more precise (“Rantah forests in Sind, (Jerruck Division)” 
<collectingCountry id="B8E97639FFBBC324FF7FFECFFEC3FEB5" box="[227,324,260,284]" name="Pakistan" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
) than the locality associated with the 
<collectionCode id="A6EFAE6CFFBBC324FD77FECEFCB8FEB5" box="[747,831,261,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">BMNH</collectionCode>
specimens (“Sind” 
<collectingCountry id="B8E97639FFBBC324FB83FECFFB04FEB5" box="[1055,1155,260,284]" name="Pakistan" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
). This mandatory change of 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFBBC324FF29FEE3FF62FEE9" box="[181,229,296,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
locality will not negatively effect the knowledge of the more specific original 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFBBC324FBC6FEE3FB0DFEE9" box="[1114,1162,296,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
locality for this species, and is considered insignificant relative to the taxonomic stability gained by the 
<typeStatus id="1F45880BFFBBC324FB8DFE86FBEDFECC" box="[1041,1130,333,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">neotype</typeStatus>
designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C04136A9FFBBC324FF59FEA4FBFAFE5D" blockId="6.[151,1437,151,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">
Regarding the nomenclature of this species, the spelling of Murray’s original name 
<taxonomicName id="07FE4D2AFFBBC324FB1DFEBAFA8CFE21" box="[1153,1291,368,392]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Hemidactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gleadowi">
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFBBC324FB1DFEBAFB12FE21" box="[1153,1173,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFBBC324FB39FEBBFA8CFE21" box="[1189,1291,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">gleadowi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was clearly intentional as he later repeats it in 
<bibRefCitation id="A46F4B58FFBBC324FDBBFE5EFD67FE05" author="Murray" box="[551,736,404,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" refString="Murray, J. A. (1884 b) Additions to the reptilian fauna of Sind. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 14, 97 - 106." type="journal article" year="1884" yearSuffix="b">
Murray (
<number id="7636248EFFBBC324FD11FE5FFD4EFE05" box="[653,713,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="1884.0">1884</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
. Boulenger’s (
<number id="7636248EFFBBC324FC1BFE5FFC46FE05" box="[903,961,404,428]" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" value="1885.0">1885</number>
) emendation of the name to 
<taxonomicName id="07FE4D2AFFBBC324FA93FE5EFA1AFE05" box="[1295,1437,404,428]" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Hemidactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="6" pageNumber="43" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gleadovii">
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFBBC324FA93FE5EFAA4FE05" box="[1295,1315,405,428]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFBBC324FAA8FE5FFA1AFE05" box="[1332,1437,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">gleadovii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was deliberate, using the emended spelling several times in the text and acknowledging the original spelling in the synonymy. According to the 
<emphasis id="F28AEABBFFBBC324FE47FE17FD91FE5D" box="[475,534,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="43">Code</emphasis>
it is an unjustified emendation of the original spelling.
</paragraph>
